+## OpenClaw-style Public Bot Profile
+
+If you want Hermes to behave like a public OpenClaw-style Feishu bot, use this combination:
+
+```bash
+FEISHU_CONNECTION_MODE=websocket
+FEISHU_ALLOW_ALL_USERS=true
+FEISHU_GROUP_POLICY=open
+FEISHU_HOME_CHANNEL=oc_xxx
+FEISHU_HOME_CHANNEL_NAME=Home
+```
+
+Behavior with this profile:
+
+- **Direct messages:** anyone can message the bot directly.
+- **Group chats:** anyone can talk to the bot, but Hermes still only engages when the bot is explicitly `@mentioned` (or `@all`, if enabled in the chat).
+- **Streaming replies:** Feishu uses Hermes's native streaming card updates with visible status and elapsed time.
+- **Notifications / cron output:** the configured home channel receives default deliveries.
+
+This is the closest native-Hermes equivalent to installing a separate OpenClaw Feishu plugin, while still keeping Hermes's own adapter, auth flow, and routing model.
+
 | Value | Behavior |
 |-------|----------|
 | `open` | Hermes responds to @mentions from any user in any group. |
